data.title: Trevor Vasey - 2014 - Football
data.meta_description: Trevor Vasey (12) QB  - 2014: Two-time selection to the Northeast-10 Conference Weekly Honor Roll... Ranked first in the Northeast-10 and eighth in the nation in
data.text:
2014: Two-time selection to the Northeast-10 Conference Weekly Honor Roll... Ranked first in the Northeast-10 and eighth in the nation in passing yards per completion with 15.21 per pass caught. Played in 10 games on the year… Completed 112-of-241 passes on the year for a 46.5 passing percentage… Threw for 1704 total yards and 13 touchdowns on the season… Finished with 81 rushes for a total of 237 yards and four rushing touchdowns… Had a pass efficiency of 116.20 and averaged 23.7 all-purpose yards per game… Threw for a season-high 303 yards vs. New Haven on 9/20/14 including a season-long 65- yard pass… Threw for three touchdowns vs. Pace on 10/10/14.

2013: At Division 1 Elon College, Vasey appeared in seven games as a wide receiver... Finished with two receptions for 15 yards vs. Georgia Southern on 11/16/13, including a long of 11 yards.

2012: At Dean College, he started nine games... Completed 101-of-206 pass attempts for 1,862 yards and 15 touchdowns... Averaged 206.9 yards per game... Posted three multi-touchdown games... Finished with a season-high 386 yards and a five touchdowns in a win over Louisburg College.

Prior to Assumption: Transferred from Division I Elon University... Also attended Hargrave Military Academy... Played football and basketball at Saint Raphael Academy... Two-time First Team All-Division football player... Two-time Second Team All-Division basketball player... Dean College Offensive Player of the Year.

Personal: Son of Todd and Kelly... Has a brother, Trent, and a sister, Kayla.
